inn1.comm: starts with a leg-stump line and it's helped towards midwicket
bit more towards the leg stump and it's tucked to the right of midwicket
just a bit towards middle and leg, nudged towards square leg now and he's off the mark
nervous charge down the track and he's struck in front of middle and leg, appeal turned down
much flatter towards the leg side, it was shorter too, and it goes off the pad very fine on the leg side
comes down again to take it on the full and flicks to midwicket
shapes it away a bit, pretty full outside off and it's pushed down to mid-off
137kmh, nice shape with middle-stump line from just back of length, Chamu manages to get his bat down just in time to tuck it to midwicket
angling down the leg side and it's helped towards fine leg easily
back of length and straight outside off, pushed off the back foot to short cover
pitches it up and nips it in towards the stumps, good pace too, and Chamu digs it out to mid-off for a quick single
beaten! This one leaves the batsman from just outside off as he looks to drive on the off side and misses
angling in towards the stumps, blocked back
angling down leg now, flatter too, and it's clipped away behind square for two easy runs
more on target towards the stumps, an inside edge onto the pads saves the batsman
presses forward and defends it back this time
takes a step down and deflects it off the pad to the leg side
flat on middle, no room at all, and it's defended off the back foot
drives away from the body, the ball shapes away from good length and beats him again!
angling in towards off stump now, no swing, and it's pushed down to mid-on
back of length this time towards off and it's clipped to mid-on off the back foot
fuller towards middle and leg, and it's flicked to mid-on again
gets a bit of room to open up his arms and drives it gently between cover point and point for two
shortish outside off and it's punched to mid off
keeps a bit low as it's angled in and Chamu whips it off the back foot to long on
leans forward for the ball that is coming in and blocks
fuller and more towards leg now, he helps it fine on the leg side for two easy runs
targets the leg stump and it's pushed down to mid-on
presses forward this time to block it back
leans forward again for the ball around off and blocks again
big bat lift and firm punch for the ball outside off, but he finds short cover
charges down and gets some room, he drives that powerfully but can't clear mid-off now
gets a short ball and this time he swivels on the back foot to pull that away to the midwicket boundary. First boundary of the match, after 33 balls
back of length outside off and it's steered to point
it's short and quick, Chamu manages some bat on it with a hook to the midwicket region
135kmh, fuller towards middle and leg, driven gently to mid-on
charges down but can't take it on the full, drives it firmly to mid off
comes down again and this time he chips it down the ground with some power, before it's cut off by long on for two
errs towards the leg side now, and Moor helps it fine on leg
good-looking cover drive for the fullish ball and he finds cover
clipped to deep midwicket as it's pitched towards middle and leg
falls short of mid-off! Chamu gave the charge for the third time this over and lofted it on the off side just a bit, but it fell wide and short of the fielder there
bangs in the short ball just outside off, he lets it go
another bouncer, this time more towards the batsman and he withdraws in the nick of time
taps the short of length ball towards cover but comes back as there's no run
angling in from further outside off, taps it into the covers again
just a bit of room with that back of length ball, and he steers it to point
good length now with some width, driven into the covers but timing wasn't that great
starts with a fullish delivery on the stumps and it's clipped towards deep midwicket
119kph, wobbly and outside off, driven a bit late into the covers
nicely driven this time, short cover dives to his left and misses. Cover point dives to his right and can't get there either and they come back for the second
much straighter and it's pushed down to mid-on
bit of width again, he guides it to point off the back foot
good over as it ends with a dot ball that was tucked to midwicket from middle stump
pretty wide outside off, he goes back and punches it down
fuller and still outside off, he leans forward, waits and helps it behind square on off
bit of yes and now as this one is driven on off, short cover dives to his left and saves a run
tries to push the ball into the covers and misses
much slower on the stumps, it's tucked to square leg now
poor delivery on the leg side, but it's simply helped to midwicket with soft hands
angling in towards the pads, tucked to long leg easily
tight line just outside off and it's punched to mid-off for a quick single
more room outside off, Chamu steers it towards point where a dive to the right saves a few runs
tucks the ball from middle stump to midwicket
much shorter but no room, right on middle, and it's defended back
that back of the hand cutter outside off, and it's pushed to mid-off
slog-sweep for the length ball well outside off gets him one
tries to drive it on off or straight even though it pitched on middle and turned in, inside edge goes to leg
another high back-lift sweep from Chamu, one behind square
keeps a bit low outside off, thick outside edge to short fine leg
much slower on the stumps, tucked to midwicket
shorter and flatter outside off, steers it straight to point
tight again on middle, it's helped to the leg side
drives the fuller and straighter ball down towards mid on
stays back and defends the back of length ball back to Mirwais
whips this one from off stump with the angle to deep square leg
slower ball at 103kh, Moor spots it and chips it towards wide long-off with a lofted drive, not much power. Rashid Khan chases it all the way and slides it in with a dive to save two
some room on the last ball and an outside edge goes to third man for one
goes for a heave on the leg side, ball was on off, and misses
nudges this one into the covers
shorter and flatter on middle, tucked to midwicket
this is slower and down the leg side, Moor looks to tickle it fine down the leg side but it's gone for five wides
outside off again, helped to point this time
much shorter outside off and it's slapped hard to cover. Kept a bit low
big lbw appeal form the bowler, even though that one probably hit him outside leg as he went for the sweep
some room outside off and it's punched to mid-off
back of length and angling in, clipped to long leg off the back foot
towards the leg side again and it's helped wide of a diving short fine leg for two more
some room outside off now, Moor drives it late to third man and that's the team 50. The run rate is picking up
defends it towards mid-on with soft hands, as mid-off runs across to pick it up
back of length on the stumps, helped to midwicket
presses forward and blocks in front of off
small step forward and nurdles this one towards midwicket
this one goes across the bat with the angle, no turn and beaten!
flatter on middle and leg with turn, worked to midwicket
gets some room on the off side and it's steered towards sweeper cover for two before Rashid chases it down
slower and straighter on off, blocked off the back foot
starts with a no ball that angled in, worked to leg
short, flat and wide, it's slammed to sweeper cover off the back foot
short outside off, tucked to the leg side for one
some flight now outside off, on good length, and he pushes and misses
more towards the stumps and it's nudged to square leg
room again with the short of length ball, slammed straight to cover now
turns the googly in from outside off, Chamu makes room and then works it down to long on
length ball on off, pushed down to long on
loud appeal for lbw as Moor tries to reverse-sweep it, misses and the umpire doesn't move. Wonder what saved him, it hit him in line and was going straight. Maybe the height
quite slow around off and Poor heaves it away to the midwicket boundary for the first six!
pushes this one off the back foot to cover
goes on the back foot and works it to leg for one more
rocks back to open up his stance, it's short and he has dispatched that over the midwicket boundary for a big six! Second of the over
leans forward and nurdles the ball to leg
tries to sweep a flighted delivery from outside off and misses. Wasn't that far from off stump
fuller outside off and it's pushed down to long on
lots of flight outside off for the googly, driven to cover before it can turn
pitched up, this one is slogged to the cow corner, third six in the last nine balls and all have been big!
goes back patiently and pushes the ball back
some flight on the off side, pushed back
comes down this time and it's chipped towards midwicket
waits and pushes the ball to leg, and Nabi runs across to stop it
goes back, the ball keeps low and it's worked to leg for one now
Moor also works the ball from outside off towards long on
goes back to allow the ball to turn, and it's helped to square leg

what did he have for drinks? Gets a length ball and sweeps it against the turn with some top-edge to the midwicket boundary for six! Went very high and got the distance too. What a way to get to his fifty
flighted outside off, he drives and misses this time
too full this time and it's driven straight to cover
turns in the googly towards off and it's punched to cover
straighter one this time outside off, turned to the leg side for one
angling in a little bit from off, tucked to the leg side
fullish around off and it's pushed back
turning in from outside off, Moor goes back and pushes to cover
reverse-sweep got some bat and it went out of the keeper's gloves to the leg side
straighter ball on length outside off, driven down to long off for one
nicely flighted on off, it's helped with the turn to leg and they scamper for one
too short from Rashid, it's pulled with some power but straight to midwicket
too full outside off now, pushed straight to cover
goes on the back foot now and it's cut to cover point. Misfield, but they don't take a second
flighted googly well outside off, he cuts and misses

that's gone high again, but he holes out this time to long-on! It was pitched up slightly, and Moor lofted it high and straight down the ground off the front foot, went high but Dawlat hardly had to move for the catch
turns in the googly towards off to end the over, it's pushed to the leg side
loud appeal for lbw as it pitches outside off and has hit the pad outside off too, appeal rightly turned down as they steal two leg byes
full outside off, driven into the off side now
shorter and wider, cut off the back foot to point
fuller now outside off and Waller chips it over the in field with a late and uppish drive, right in the gap for four
gets forward and defends it to midwicket
low full toss outside off, driven firmly to long-off
gets to the pitch of the ball, covers the line nicely to drive to sweeper cover
too full, drifting into middle, cramped for room, gets a thick edge back onto the pad
leans forward and crunches that wide of the deep cover fielder, excellent running between the wickets
squared up by the sharp turn from outside off, he was prodding forward without any conviction. Cracking ball
swept powerfully, gets it fine, good work by Rashid Khan at fine leg, had to dish in a full length dive to pull it back in
dabbed with soft hands to the off side
steps out and chips it into the gap between deep midwicket and long-on
flicked with the spin to deep midwicket
opens the face of the bat and dabs it wide of the short third man fielder
done in by sharp turn, missed the flick, big appeal for lbw but umpire Vineet Kulkarni reckons it was spinning down leg. He's got it spot on
pushed through on middle, driven to long-off
steps out and whips it away against the spin to long on
lovely flight this time, lures him forward, Waller has the line well covered
beaten by sharp turn and bounce. It was short, he shaped to cut but the ball just skid on
angled to short third man, who fires a rocket throw back to the 'keeper
driven with the spin to cover, end of another tight over
trots down the track and lofts that up nicely by taking it on the full, and strikes it just wide of lone long for a straight six!
flatter on the off stump and it's tucked to midwicket
bit of offspin again and it's worked to the leg side
loudish appeal for lbw as it hits him around off but he was on the front foot and it had good bounce too
some room on the off side, it's tapped behind square on the off side
gets room and makes a lot room by backing away to slam it to sweeper cover for one
comes down and chips it straight down the ground, without much force and gets two
some width and it's struck straight to cover
shorter and on the pads, tucked square on the leg side for one and that's a fifty for Chibhabha too, off 86 balls
wider outside off and it's driven to sweeper cover for one more
touch shorter and flatter on off, he takes a tiny step down and clips it to midwicket
tries to drill the length ball through the covers and misses

catch taken at second attempt in Cape Town and it's the same in Sharjah too - he's cut it straight to point. It was short outside off, he cut it fiercely off the back foot and Hashmatullah Shahidi tried to take it over his head with both hands, the ball popped out and took it comfortably the second time
shortish outside off and it's pushed straight to cover
on length now, no room again and it's defended on the off side
just back of length on off, Masakadza on the back foot and punches it down to mid on
punched off the back foot through the off side and he's off the mark
bit of room and it's punched down to long off
comes down the track and chips it to long on
much straighter with some turn and it's defended back
takes a step down to flick it to leg, and gets an edge to the off side
almost from in front of the umpire, pitches it also in front of the stumps and Masakadza nurdles it to leg
chipped this time down the ground to long on
drives it from outside off to the left of mid off for one
better delivery on the off stump, on good length, he still manages it in the gap between cover point and point
defends the straighter ball back to the bowler
another tight ball and this one is punched to cover
tries to hammer it down the ground but finds mid off
bit too straight and full, Masakadza lofts it straight over the bowler's head off the middle of the bat for four!
towards leg, he tries to sweep and takes it on the pad
shortish, he goes back and pulls it to deep midwicket. They were looking for the second, but there was no time
tries the reverse sweep and gets some bat and pad to slip, after a bounce, of course
that nearly hurried through him as he went on the back foot, got some bat to short fine leg and responded well for the single

great catch from the captain and look at that beaming smile! Chibhabha went for a slog-sweep when the ball wasn't that full, he tried to go over midwicket but Stanikzai jumped and plucked it out with one hand!
short and flat on off, pulled to deep backward square
Mirwais nips it in towards off and Mutumbami blocks it back
nicely driven from outside off, but straight to cover
seaming in again from outside off, blocked on the off side
touch fuller towards off, dangerously flicked to midwicket
pushed just wide of cover who runs to his left and gets to it but can't avoid the quick single
angling in towards the batsman, nudged down to long on for one
he pokes his bat out for the leggie and is beaten
goes for a big sweep for the ball that was way too wide, and luckily gets an edge past the keeper on the off side before it's cut off at third man with a chase from Mirwais
poor and short googly with lots of room, he slams it to deep cover
better googly, fuller and closer to the batsman, who tries to cut and misses
flatter and closer, but still wide of off, he tried to turn it to leg but defended it back
short again, Mutumbami muscles it to the leg side with a pull and a fantastic effort at deep midwicket makes them earn the second
not too much width outside off and it's defended to cover
touch fuller and it's driven firmly to the same fielder
much straighter and touch shorter, nurdled to midwicket now
dropped by the captain now! Masakadza made room and lofted it with a drive, it went pretty flat, and Asghar put in a dive to his left but couldn't hold on to it
fifth dot ball as the batsman pushes another length ball into the covers
yorks him on the last ball, and Masakadza avoids a maiden by digging it out to long on
reverse swing into the batsman from Dawlat, Masakadza gets an inside edge onto the pad for a single
he sees room and throws his arms at it, gets an inside edge just past the keeper's left for a cheeky four
absolutely straight now and it's drilled back to the bowler, the ball goes off his left boot to long on for one
angling in towards HM, he defends it back
dances down, it's a full toss on the pads and he flicks it away with some force, in the big gap between midwicket and mid-on for a four
back of length outside off, he taps it to backward point
steps out and wrists it against the spin to long on
chipped back over the bowler's head
forces that one through the off side, towards wide long-off
waits for the ball to turn away as he nurdles it behind square on the leg side
drifts in and spins away, closes the bat face a little early, the leading edge lands short of point
tucked off the back foot to the on side

fro wide of the crease on leg stump, Masakadza sweeps off the middle of the bat and Karim does well to slide to his right in the deep from deep backward square, he gets to it but the ball goes through for four
shortish and turning away, Masakadza taps it back
presses forward to defend and he's beaten, Shahzad appeals all alone
straighter and flatter on off, it's punched back
drifting in with some flight towards middle, it's struck hard and back as Rashid dives to get his hands to it
full again and this time it's driven down to long on
another one down, this time it's Masakadza caught! It was short and wide, Masakadza slammed it with hard hands through the off side and Nabi jumped at cover to catch it with both hands
on the off side and Chigumbura defends it back
fuller on off and it's driven down to long off. Off the mark
flighted, dipping and full on the stumps, he pushes it to leg for one
full on off and it's driven easily to wide long off
bit of width around off and he runs it down to third man
on the pads, he tries to flick it away but gets a leg bye
reverse-swinging in a bit, he dabs it towards point for a quick single and succeeds
some more width and it's steered firmly to sweeper cover for one
superb inswinging yorker right on the middle stump, Chiggy blocks it down to mid off
that's through mid-off's fiedlers for four! It was full and swinging in, Chiggy drilled in the drive and it went straight to mid-off, but also through his legs. Makes it eight from the over
from wide of the crease and outside off, punched to long off
presses forward and blocks it bluntly
shuffles across and comes down, he taps it towards short midwicket, off the pad, from the off side for a quick single

fifth one down, all caught! Mutumbami went down on a knee to sweep that fullish delivery to the leg side, he didn't muscle that very well and Shafiqullah had to dive to his right to get his fingers under it as the ball was dipping. Well done after that misfield in the last over
turns it away nicely from off, away from the batsman, and Raza opens the face of the bat to help it to off
angled in this time and it's tucked without moving his feet to leg
shapes it in nicely towards the stumps, keeps a bit low, and Raza defends on off
doesn't get his body behind the ball but manages to steer it dangerously from middle stump into the covers
right on target on the off side, dabbed towards cover for a quick single
superb shot from Raza! Full and outside off, some inswing, and Raza lofts it away over the covers from the middle of the bat, to just beat sweeper cover for four
nips it into the batsman from back of length, tapped towards cover for another quick one
attempted yorker is a full toss on the pads and Chiggy helps it away behind square, just wide of short fine leg and gets four more. Big over for Zimbabwe
flighted outside off and it's driven straight to cover
tossed up outside off again, he leans into it and dabs it to point
misses out on a full toss! It was flighted on off, he swept and only got an edge onto his pad
short googly turning in, Raza swipes it to backward square
covers the stumps and defends the length ball towards point

what a way to end the over, Chigumbura is plumb! It was tossed up on the middle stump, nicely flighted, and Chigumbura went for what looked like a premeditated sweep, missed it completely and was trapped right in front of middle
doesn't give any room, but Raza makes some and pushes it into the covers
full on the stumps, flicked to deep midwicket for one

inside edge onto the stumps, Raza is gone too! There wasn't much room and the ball nipped in too from outside off, Raza stayed back and tried to steer it to third man with a horizontal bat but got a bottom edge onto the off stump
what a good looking drive on the first ball, Cremer drives it nicely wide of extra cover in the gap
Dawlat appeals for lbw even as Cremer was hit around the waist after he missed the pull. The umpire jokes by signalling with his hand that it was going over the batsman's head
almost in the block hole outside off, inside edge goes behind square on leg for one
full and hardly outside off, driven down to long off
slower one at 107kph, right on the off stump and Jongwe defends it back
what an outrageous shot from Jongwe! He got into position for a reverse sweep and then unleashed a reverse-flick behind square for four!
shuffles across to off and taps the ball towards deep midwicket for one
fuller now around off it's driven down to long on
back of length towards off, he waits and runs it down to third man
full now from Dawlat and it's drilled straight to cover
short ball this time outside off, he tries to pull, probably didn't expect it, and misses it completely
short ball again, this time closer to Cremer and he pulls it wide of long on
slower legcutter towards the pads, Cremer spots it nicely and slams it with good timing, to the right of deep midwicket for a one-bounce four

another good catch taken over the head! Cremer got a full delivery and wanted to clear mid-off, he lofted it alright but Nabi backpedalled a few steps and took it very well over his head with both hands
turns in the googly from outside off, appeals for lbw but it struck him outside off
makes it a full toss by coming down and drives through the covers
backs away, then comes back and pulls the short ball between long on and deep midwicket
similar approach from Jongwe and he cuts the googly straight to backward point
excellent stop with a dive to his left, from Rashid, after the ball was pushed back from Jongwe
he takes the reverse-scoop out of the bag again, and sends it flying over the two fielders in the circle behind square on the off side. That makes it five from the over
there's some width on the off side, he dances down to slam it away but misses
he connects this time and it's almost gone all the way! Too full this time and Madziva got the chance to swing his arms, and drilled it through the air and over the covers
taps the slower delivery to point and takes off for a quick single. He was probably out if the fielder had hit the stumps at the bowler's end

that's gone down third man's throat, third wicket for Dawlat! 140kpmh and it was a short ball, Jongwe pulled and was beaten by pace, the ball took the top edge and flew to Mirwais, who hardly had to move
bangs in the short ball and he ducks under it
backs away and Dawlat follows him with a bouncer, and he ducks again
Chisoro bowled first ball, they are all out for 226! It was on the leg stump and he went for a heave but missed completely, the ball gets the top of leg stump

inn2.comm: what a way to start the chase! Gets some width and it's full and he creams that through the covers with an exquisite cover drive! Such style
hops back now and defends the back of length ball on off
seams the short of length ball in and Noor Ali dabs it to midwicket
shortish and wide, not much bounce so that goes under his bat as he goes for a big swing
much better length and bounce this time, punched straight to cover
another first wicket for Madziva in the first over! Width again, it was nipping away and Noor Ali chased it without moving his feet and got an inside edge straight to the keeper
blocks the straight ball on the stumps
pushes a simple full toss down to mid off
on the middle stump on length and it's tucked to midwicket
he misses out again as it's wide outside off and he finds cover point
connects well this time and drives that nicely from full-length, in the gap between cover point and point for four to get off the mark
drives another full delivery, but finds cover again
presses forward on his first ball and blocks the length ball into the covers
bit of inswing with the length ball from outside off, he pushes at it and gets a thick edge to leg
keeps his head down again and blocks another one on off
slashes the shorter ball which had width, to cover point now at the circle
goes on the back foot and punches this one down to mid off
more room this time but he barely moves his feet and cuts it straight to the fielder again
tucks the ball square on the leg side for one
flatter one at 94kph down the leg side for a wide, past the sweep
much better now on the off stump on length, blocked back
on middle now, Asghar defends again and it was in the air for half a second
much fuller now and it's driven straight to cover
dipping full toss on middle, he drives and gets an inside edge to leg
drives this one much better down to mid-off for a single
shapes it in at 123kph from well outside off, he defends with a thick inner edge to leg
bottom-edges it to the keeper but it fell at least a couple of yards ahead of him. Was wide, he chased and it didn't bounce much
dabs this straighter one down to mid on for a quick single
132.7kph, too full outside off and Shahzad drives it straight down to mid off
seaming in from back of length, and he slices it late to third man
wicket off a full toss, straight to midwicket, oh my! It was angling in towards the pads and was much below waist-height, and he clipped it straight to Chibhabha, who had given a catch to Asghar!
pretty slow on off stump, he goes back and defends to leg
quicker at 92.6kmh on off stump, defends it back now
beats him this time! Some turn for the length ball outside off, drawing Shahzad forward to defend, and it turned away
much straighter and he blocks it off the middle now
errs down the leg side, goes past the sweep for a wide
leans forward again and pushes the turning ball into the covers
doesn't move much this time and taps the ball into the covers for a quick single
straight delivery well outside off, Shahzad doesn't bother
swinging in from short of length and Shahzad hops back to work it to midwicket
what a shot from Shahzad! It was a slower legcutter on length outside off, Shahzad picks it early and slogs it away with some force to the cow corner for a one-bounce four!
looks to slam that off the back foot but finds point with some bottom edge
in the block hole on the stumps and it's pushed to mid on with a straight bat
gets some room this time and runs that one down to third man
100kph and towards off stump, and Shahzad's bat comes down just in time to defend that
100kph and wide outside off, left alone now
leans forward into it to defend it on off
shorter and wider, he slices it off the back foot to point
much quicker at 104kph now and Shahzad chops it away beyond short third man in the gap
pretty short and angling in towards off, he goes back and defends
bouncer down the leg side and he ducks under it. Not a wide as it probably went over the batsman
gets room and Rashid puts his second ball away with a spectacular square cut, absolutely square of the wicket, over the in field for four
not too wide and he slams it square again, but doesn't middle it this time
another smashing shot! Room again, this one back of length, and he stays back to punch it square, just to backward point's right for four
gets a straighter ball and patiently defends it this time
nicely driven down to mid-off with a straight bat, but straight to the fielder
short and quick towards off, Shahzad defends it down to long on
shorter outside off, it's driven to extra cover
leans forward a bit and defends the straight ball
presents the straight bat again and the ball comes in just a bit to take inside edge and pad before going behind square on leg
presses forward and helps the ball into the covers
angles it in sharply towards middle and leg, clipped straight to midwicket
back of length outside off and that's cut off the back foot to cover point
drives the fuller ball on off and a thick outside edge rolls away wide of backward point for one
shortish outside off with room, he taps it late to third man

what a catch from the big man, Hamilton Masakadza! That beauty from Jongwe squared up Rashid Khan as it just about held its line, after coming in with the angle. Rashid offered a straight bat and a thick outside edge flew towards point, where Masakadza put in a forward dive rightwards to get both hands under it
back of length now outside off and it's defended safely to backward point
some turn on the off stump and it's blocked back
presses forward and defends before it can turn
goes back this time and clips it off the back foot and the pads to square leg
gets off the mark by driving that down to long off easily
nicely tossed up on the off stump, he defends it back
just a touch shorter to let the ball turn, and Shahzad presses forward to negate it
angling in towards the pads, clipped to long leg for one
back of length and with the angle, it's dabbed towards midwicket now
gives some room this time, it was short of length, and he slices it to backward point
130kmh, on length and well outside off, Nabi defends into the covers
works this one from back of length to cover point
stays on the back foot and defends it on the off side
good turn for the shortish ball from middle towards off, Shahzad stays back and taps it down to long off
pitched up a little bit and Nabi defends towards point
easily pushes the full ball down to long on
nicely flighted, but full on the stumps, Shahzad pushes it back
tossed up outside off and Shahzad watches it turn into the keeper's gloves
falls just short of short fine leg! It was a straighter one down leg, he pulled and it the fielder tried with a forward dive, but it was out of his reach. And the ball went through him to long leg
what a shot from Nabi! He gets room outside off and swings his arms with a big follow through, through the covers for four
that's wide outside off, marginally inside the line, but it's called a wide
fuller outside off and it's driven to sweeper cover for one
defends a back of length ball solidly to cover
chops the back of length ball from close to the off stump to third man
angling in towards the pads, and it's helped along to fine leg, it brings up the team 50
bit too full and Nabi drives it handsomely to sweeper cover for one
sweeps the ball against the turn to short fine leg and a dive saves a few runs
presses forward patiently to block that one
stumping appeal, Mutumbami looks confident! the ball turned away just a bit as the batsman swept and missed, and the keeper took the bails off quickly but Nabi's back foot was back in the crease
lbw appeal this time but it was going down leg, maybe over too. Nabi went back to work it to leg, and the ball pitched outside leg before hitting the pad high
back to the forward lean and he defends this time

the googly gets Nabi, another big wicket gone! Nabi went on the back foot to make some room and target the off side, but the ball came in just a bit from outside off, got an inside edge and disturbed the stumps
leans into it on the off side and defends it back
defends this one back solidly with a straight bat
stays back and turns the back of length ball to the leg side
covers the stumps and defends the short of length ball on off
goes for a wild heave on the leg side, ball was on off and he misses it completely!

stays in the crease and defends it back to the bowler to make it a maiden. Jongwe throws the ball back to rattle the stumps, even though Shahzad was well in, and the batsman raises his arms wondering why that happened
length ball on off is defended to the off side
sharp turn brings the ball back into the batsman and it's worked off the pad behind square on leg for two
googly around off, he went back and didn't pick it, but adjusted well to swat it square on the leg side
pretty full on off and it's driven down easily to long off
turns it in sharply to the stumps, the batsman covers and defends
turns it in again, too short this time and Shahidi pulls it in the air but it lands a few metres short of deep midwicket
the angle gets a thick edge off the left-hander's bat and it's gone wide of slip to third man
too much room, too short and Shahzad slams it over the point fielder with a powerful cut for four. Landed just before the rope
almost in the block hole outside off, Shahzad pushes it gently to cover
taps this back of length ball towards backward point

what an effort from Raza, excellent fielding and a direct hit but looks like Shahidi made it with a dive! Oh, is his bat in the air? Shahzad tapped the ball into the covers with soft hands and took off quickly, Shahidi responded with some hesitation but went ahead and a direct hit with a forward dive from Raza running in meant Shahidi had to dive and slide his bat. His bat was partially in the air, but looks like some of it was in the crease. Replays are not so conclusive, so some benefit of doubt too
stays back in the crease and defends the ball angling away into the covers
full ball drifting into the player, driven down to long on
too full on the stumps, good flight though, and Cremer dives to his left to stop that as it was pushed back
better length now - allows the ball to turn in from outside off and it's defended off the back foot
bit too full again outside off, driven straight to cover off the front foot
fullish again, driven to cover with another forward lean
turns it in a bit with a marginally shorter length and it's blocked back
some bounce for the length ball on the pads, the ball lobs up towards square leg
goes back in the crease and tucks the ball towards midwicket for one
gets room on the off side and it's cut off the back foot to sweeper cover
flatter and outside off with the angle, swatted down to long on
flighted full toss on leg and it's swept straight to long leg for one
better ball - on length on the stumps and it's pushed to midwicket
flighted on the off stump, pushed down to long-on
flatter outside off, and he goes back to defend it close to the pitch
goes back and across and helps the ball with the turn to deep backward
81kph, bit of turn from length and Shahzad blocks it back
flighted and full, Shahzad sweeps it away, it's in the air but well over short fine leg and in the gap for four
goes on the back foot to cut, but that went through and nearly got the off stump
pushes the fuller ball into the covers now
presses forward a lot, the ball turns away from length and beats his outside edge
goes back now, waits for it to turn an cuts to cover point
straighter towards the stumps and it's defended back
puts his front foot forward and lets the ball turn away from him
length delivery outside off and it's defended into the covers
closer to the off stump and it's driven on off again
angling into pads, clipped to deep midwicket and he wants second but there's no time
too much room outside off and Shahidi slices it off the back foot, past point, and in the gap for two
goes on the front foot and dabs this one to point
closer to the off stump, he punches it off the back foot to point again
on the pads and it's clipped to deep midwicket for two in the gap
fuller on the pads now, he sweeps without any follow through and that went in the air, but in the gap towards deep square leg
angling in a bit and he pushes it down to long on
bit too full with some room and Shahzad drives that nicely in the gap with his wrists, and he beats long off for four
poor, flat delivery turning down leg for a wide
more room on the off side now and he slices that to backward point where a fumble from diving Masakadza gives a run
he presses forward and blocks the ball on off
drives nicely with the wrists, straight to cover
much straighter now and he defends it to midwicket
goes further towards the leg side and he pulls to find short fine leg

loud appeal and Shahzad is plumb, big wicket for Zimbabwe! Chibhabha brought ball in from well outside off and Shahzad dangerously went back, right in front of the stumps, to work it to leg, but missed and the ball hit him in front of middle
pretty wide outside off, he lets it go to the keeper
much straighter towards the off stump now and he blocks it back. It's a wicket maiden
just outside off and he defends it back
some room now and he goes back to cut it to point
back in the crease again and pushed to cover this time
tossed up nicely, he defends off the front foot and gets an inside edge to leg for one
turning in from well outside off, he leans into it to help it to leg
more towards off and middle, he goes across and nudges it fine on the leg side for two in the gap
no room for the length ball around off, blocked back
120kph, right on the off stump again, the batsman defends it back
gets some room to breathe and cuts it away to third man for one
he shuffles across but Chibhabha errs down leg for a wide
goes across again and blocks the ball back solidly
covers his stumps and defends the straight ball back
stifled appeal as he's hit on the pad but in front of leg, and it was going down leg with the angle
presses forward and blocks the ball into the off side
goes back to cut it and sends it just wide of slip in the gap
nicely flighted around off and he drives it back to Raza
some turn outside off as Shahidi leans forward to defend and gets a thickish edge behind square
a bottom-edge this time off the back foot as he looks to cut it to point
comes on the front foot now and drives it into the covers
tries to slog the length delivery into the leg side and only gets an inside edge to square leg
beautifully bowled outside off with the angle, nearly took the outside edge and went for byes off the keeper's gloves
back of length around off and it's defended to the leg side
reaches out a bit and defends it into the covers for a quick signle
angles it away from the off stump and nearly gets the outside edge again
dabs the short of length ball from off stump to cover for a quick single
errs down the leg side, past the sweep and they get a bye too
down the leg side again, but is he stumped? Sadiq was on the move when the ball went past him and Mutumbami did well to whip the bails off, but his left leg came back in a jiffy
blocks this one back to the bowler
keeps a bit low on middle and leg, and it's clipped to leg for one
nice flight and turn outside off, he doesn't bother
further outside off with more turn and he lets it go again
short outside off now, he goes back and across and powers that through the leg side, with a pull, for a four against the turn
Chibhabha does it again, and another batsman is caught! Sadiq drove the length ball in the air off the front foot and could not clear mid-off, where Chisoro went back a few steps to take it easily
risky second run, but he makes it. He pushed at the ball and it went behind square off a thick inside edge, and they had to hurry back for the second
defends this one more confidently to the off side

the third one for Chibhabha, outside edge well-taken by the keeper! He angled it in from outside off, Shafiqullah poked at it and played inside the line as the ball kissed the outside edge and Mutumbami celebrated as soon as he caught it
right in the block hole now, and the ball goes behind square after an inside edge
bit too full and it's driven nicely past extra cover for one
pitches it short and wide outside off and Mirwais goes back to punch that very well through the covers for four!
some turn now outside off, there's an outside edge too, but well wide of slip and to the third-man boundary for four
another poor delivery - flat and wide with some turn, Mirwais only gets a bottom edge this time
flatter one at 100kph towards off, Mirwais defends off the back foot
reaches out for the widish delivery and drives into the covers
much straighter on off, Mirwais puts his head down, elbow high and presents a straight bat
right on target on the off stump, defended into the off side
shorter on the off stump, he stays back and taps it to point
pretty tight line around off, he helps it to point again
gets a bit of room and he cashes in by punching it late past backward point
pushes the length ball into the covers off the front foot
on the leg stump from back of length, helped to leg behind square for one
blocks it back solidly off the front foot from off stump
more towards the middle stump now and it's pushed back to Chisoro

down the leg side past the batsman, and looks like Mutumbami has been hit on the knee. He went down the leg side with the ball and the angle of his body exposed the knee which was actually behind the pad. He was down in a second
leans into the ball on off and defends into the covers
makes some room and steers the ball to point
bit of room, no change in approach as it's pushed to cover
fullish on the off side and it's driven into the covers easily
back of length on the off stump, pushed down to long on for one
a rare short ball from Chibhabha and it's pulled away using the pace of the ball, behind square on the leg side for a four
right on target on the middle stumps, he blocks this time
on length on the stumps and it's defended back
bit short outside off with the angle and it's pulled to deep backward now
turning into the batsman from outside off and it's pushed to midwicket
shorter and turning in again, he helps it to leg off the back foot
flighted full toss on leg, pulled but not with much power to deep square leg
flighted and full around off, pushed down easily to long off
goes back and across and it's worked off the pads for one more
comes down to slog and gets an inside edge to long on for one
fullish on the off stump, driven gently down to mid off
bit shorter and wider outside off, he defends off the back foot now
much shorter delivery and it allows the batsman to punch it to sweeper cover now
short ball angling away, he pulls and mistimes and it to midwicket
well outside the off stump and it's helped to backward point
much wider from good-length and it's driven late to backward point
flighted on off, gets a thick outside edge off a cover drive to third man
turning into the batsman from off, pushed back to Cremer

Cremer has done it, traps Shahidi lbw! It turned in from outside off as Shahidi went across and covered his stumps. He missed and the ball hit him almost in front of off stump. Could have been marginally outside too
bets him first ball with a beauty! Tossed up outside off, he presses forward to defend and the turn goes past the outside edge
leans into it again and blocks the ball back from off stump
much slower through the air on off, he brings the bat down with some hesitation and gets a thick edge to off
pretty straight on the off stump, it's pushed back to the bowler
some room on the off side and it was short too, taps it in the air to third man
pretty straight and low on the middle stump, he stays back and nurdles it to midwicket
pretty straight delivery and he replies with a straight-bat shot, too. Just past the bowler for one
back of length and angling in, worked down to mid-on
length delivery on the off stump and Dawlat responds with a defensive stroke
nice flight and drift on the off stump, he drives it down with the spin to long off
slogs the flighted delivery from the middle stump, inside edge goes behind square on leg
shortish now and turning away, he cuts it off the back foot to sweeper cover
Mirwais comes down the track and tries to slog, finds midwicket
comes down the track and he drills that by taking it on the full, right through the mid-on region for four!
on the off side now - gets a shortish ball, he rocks back and punches that with some power through the covers for another fierce four!
number four for Chibhabha, Mirwais slogs and Chibhabha hits! It was angling in towards the off stump, Mirwais played the wrong line completely with his slog and that rammed into the off stump
just outside the off stump and he defends it towards cover
some more width and that's driven to sweeper cover to get off the mark
right on the off stump now and it's pushed to midwicket
pretty straight again on the off stump, blocked back to the bowler
full on the pads, it's flicked away nicely in the air and behind square on the leg side

the straighter one goes through everything! Pitched on length around off and that went through the gap between bat and pad, and then through the keeper for four byes. A fielder chases, puts in a dive but that only rams the ball into the ad cones at the boundary
charges down, gets some bat and lofts it down the ground, but it falls well short of long on
googly turns into the batsman, and he's cramped for room to put it away
comes down again and slogs, gets some bat on that to the leg side
dances down, Cremer sends it down slower and Dawlat pushes it down gently to long on
back of length on off and it's pushed into the covers
pretty wide outside off and shaping away further, he steers it away to cover point
flicked in the air off the pads and that's gone in the gap wide of long-on for two
in the block hole around off, he blocks it to the leg side
pretty wide outside off and it's steered towards point now
pokes and misses outside off, it was back of length and he went after it but missed
in the block hole around off, Dawlat blocks it back
angled in towards the off stump, blocked back to the bowler again
drives it away from the body without moving his feet and misses!
tries a yorker and it goes down leg for a wide
back of length now outside off, punched into the covers
extra bounce surprises Hamza as he looked to defend off the back foot and took it on the glove eventually
that's the last one, caught at mid-off! Hamza chipped the length ball in the air and straight to Waller for a simple catch. Zimbabwe win by 65 runs
